cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE

The paper proposes a deep neural network for classifying glitches in gravitational-wave data. This involves visualizing glitches as spectrograms and using image classification techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Signal Processing). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as deep neural networks, which suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves image classification techniques, which suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves classification tasks, which suggests it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which suggests it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
